.git
dist
# `build` belongs here for the same reason `dist` does: both are generated and
# gitignored. Omitting it (until #2567) let `COPY . .` sweep the host's stale
# build/tokens.css into the context, so the image built on the one machine that
# had run `tokens:build` by hand and nowhere else. Excluding it forces the
# Dockerfile to generate what it needs, which is the only way the build stays
# honest.
build
